Vol / Page: 200
Edition: 1932
Quote: This was a very solitary station - on the banks of a river in a very deep valley surrounded with lofty timber of various kinds, and a day's journey from any native village or farm - our only companions being men in a state of nature, some of them having never seen a vessel or ever visited the missionary settlement.
